    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Ah, Simplicity</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Dorothy Prelinger comments on June 29 article, which described Manhattan apartment of Christopher Gow, who decorates it with sea shells silver-plated in Italy (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>I was dismayed to read of Christopher Gow (''Shhh. Hear the Surf in Midtown?'' June 29), who decorates his apartment with and sells seashells silver-plated in Italy. The only more blatant example of gilding the lily I can think of is the White Queen in ''Through the Looking Glass,'' who orders roses to be painted.</p>
        <p>DOROTHY PRELINGER  New Haven</p>
      </block>
